{"article_id":"QyjoQNYyo7hrWh6G","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Despite a lively question-and-answer session for the first of this week ' s two historic gay marriage cases ,","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"the nine Supreme Court justices on Tuesday offered no clear clues","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"on whether they will back traditional marriage","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"or affirm the right to same-sex unions","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"- or just kick the judicial can down the road .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"Tuesday ' s case could settle the standoff in California over gay marriage ,","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"and the second case ,","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"to be argued Wednesday ,","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"challenges a federal law","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"that only recognizes marriages of one man and one woman ,","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"preventing gay couples from accessing the benefits","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"afforded straight couples .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"Taken together ,","depth":4},{"id":13,"text":"the two cases could permit the nation ' s highest court to answer important questions about the legality of gay marriage and how sexual orientation should be treated","depth":5},{"id":14,"text":"when equal rights are an issue .","depth":5},{"id":15,"text":"Thousands of protesters for and against gay marriage gathered at the Capitol and Supreme Court","depth":3},{"id":16,"text":"to make their voices heard .","depth":3},{"id":17,"text":"On Tuesday , in a packed courtroom , the high court heard oral arguments in Hollingsworth v. Perry , a case","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"involving the constitutionality of Proposition 8 , a voter-passed California initiative","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"that defines marriage as only the unions of one man and one woman .","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"A key area of inquiry was what would happen","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"if the court struck down Proposition 8 .","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"SEE ALSO :","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"Both sides optimistic , uncertain","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"as gay marriage arguments end","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"Would the ruling be limited to legalizing gay marriage in California ?","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"justices asked .","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"Or would it also force a few other states","depth":13},{"id":28,"text":"that have domestic partnerships or civil unions","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"to convert them to marriage ?","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"Or would it become a national ruling ,","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"forcing all states to strike down their man-woman marriage laws ?","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"\" The problem with the case is that you ' re really asking ,","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"particularly because of the sociological evidence","depth":13},{"id":34,"text":"you cite ,","depth":13},{"id":35,"text":"for us to go into uncharted waters , \"","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"observed Associate Justice Anthony M. Kennedy .","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"Former Solicitor General Theodore B. Olson ,","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"representing two same-sex couples","depth":14},{"id":39,"text":"who want to overturn Proposition 8 ,","depth":14},{"id":40,"text":"responded","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"that the high court had ventured into the unknown in 1967","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"when it struck down laws","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"banning interracial marriage .","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"Mr. Olson ' s answer wasn ' t completely satisfying for Justice Kennedy ,","depth":13},{"id":45,"text":"but he and the other justices moved on ,","depth":13},{"id":46,"text":"posing a wide range of questions to Mr. Olson ; Charles J. Cooper ,","depth":14},{"id":47,"text":"who represented Dennis Hollingsworth and other supporters of Proposition 8 ;","depth":14},{"id":48,"text":"and Solicitor General Donald B. Verrilli Jr. ,","depth":14},{"id":49,"text":"who came as a friend of the court in support of Mr. Olson ' s side .","depth":14},{"id":50,"text":"Mr. Cooper was asked about the legal injuries to some 37,000 children","depth":14},{"id":51,"text":"being raised by gay couples","depth":15},{"id":52,"text":"who can not marry .","depth":15},{"id":53,"text":"\" The voice of those children is important in this case ,","depth":15},{"id":54,"text":"don ' t you think ? \"","depth":15},{"id":55,"text":"asked Justice Kennedy .","depth":14},{"id":56,"text":"Mr. Cooper ' s answer was","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"that there wasn ' t any data on such a subject .","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"Associate Justice Stephen G. Breyer also wanted to know","depth":15},{"id":59,"text":"why marriage - as a procreative institution - is not good for gay couples but OK for opposite-sex couples","depth":16},{"id":60,"text":"who can ' t have children .","depth":16},{"id":61,"text":"\" Couples","depth":17},{"id":62,"text":"that aren ' t gay","depth":18},{"id":63,"text":"but can ' t have children","depth":18},{"id":64,"text":"get married all the time , \"","depth":16},{"id":65,"text":"Justice Breyer said to Mr. Cooper .","depth":15},{"id":66,"text":"\" The concern is that redefining marriage as a genderless institution will sever its abiding connection to its historic traditional , procreative purposes , \"","depth":15},{"id":67,"text":"Mr. Cooper replied .","depth":15},{"id":68,"text":"It ' s also a concern ,","depth":16},{"id":69,"text":"he added ,","depth":16},{"id":70,"text":"to have the age-old institution of marriage refocused \" away from the raising of children \" to something","depth":16},{"id":71,"text":"that meets the \" emotional needs and desires of adults . \"","depth":16},{"id":72,"text":"Proposition 8 ,","depth":15},{"id":73,"text":"Mr. Olson said ,","depth":15},{"id":74,"text":"\" walls off \" marriage from gay and lesbian couples ,","depth":15},{"id":75,"text":"\" labeling their most cherished relationships as second-rate , different , unequal and not OK . \"","depth":15},{"id":76,"text":"But then he was asked pointedly","depth":15},{"id":77,"text":"if California gay couples","depth":17},{"id":78,"text":"-","depth":18},{"id":79,"text":"who already have all the rights and responsibilities in marriage in domestic partnerships -","depth":18},{"id":80,"text":"are just after the \" label \" of marriage .","depth":16},{"id":81,"text":"Since they have every other right ,","depth":16},{"id":82,"text":"\" all","depth":18},{"id":83,"text":"you ' re interested in is the label","depth":18},{"id":84,"text":"and you insist on changing the definition of the label .","depth":17},{"id":85,"text":"It ' s just about the label , \"","depth":16},{"id":86,"text":"Chief Justice John G. Roberts Jr. said .","depth":16},{"id":87,"text":"Mr. Olson countered","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"by saying","depth":14},{"id":89,"text":"that \" there are certain labels in this country","depth":16},{"id":90,"text":"that are very , very critical , \"","depth":16},{"id":91,"text":"and marriage has \" a status . \"","depth":15},{"id":92,"text":"Chief Justice Roberts agreed ,","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"but added","depth":14},{"id":94,"text":"that \" maybe it is the procreative aspect","depth":15},{"id":95,"text":"that makes it a fundamental right . \"","depth":15},{"id":96,"text":"Even the brief history of gay marriage was delved into ,","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"with Associate Justice Samuel Anthony Alito Jr. noting","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"that such nuptials are \" newer than cellphones or the Internet , \"","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"while Associate Justice Antonin Scalia repeatedly asked Mr. Olson about exactly \" when \" it become unconstitutional to prohibit gays from marriage .","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"\" We don ' t prescribe law for the future .","depth":16},{"id":101,"text":"We decide what the law is , \"","depth":16},{"id":102,"text":"said Justice Scalia .","depth":15},{"id":103,"text":"\" I ' m curious","depth":16},{"id":104,"text":"- when did it become unconstitutional to exclude homosexual couples from marriage ?","depth":17},{"id":105,"text":"1791 ?","depth":18},{"id":106,"text":"1868 ,","depth":19},{"id":107,"text":"when the 14th Amendment was adopted ? \"","depth":19},{"id":108,"text":"Mr. Olson tried to answer rhetorically ,","depth":16},{"id":109,"text":"saying","depth":17},{"id":110,"text":"the same could be asked of school segregation and interracial-marriage bans .","depth":17},{"id":111,"text":"\" Don ' t give me a question to my question , \"","depth":14},{"id":112,"text":"Justice Scalia replied ,","depth":14},{"id":113,"text":"but","depth":17},{"id":114,"text":"even as the audience laughed ,","depth":18},{"id":115,"text":"the justice pressed again on ,","depth":18},{"id":116,"text":"asking again ,","depth":17},{"id":117,"text":"\" when \" did the Constitution change on marriage ? \"","depth":17},{"id":118,"text":"There ' s no specific date in time , \"","depth":17},{"id":119,"text":"Mr. Olson finally responded .","depth":17},{"id":120,"text":"\" This is an evolutionary cycle . \"","depth":16},{"id":121,"text":"\" Well , how am I supposed to know","depth":18},{"id":122,"text":"how to decide a case ...","depth":18},{"id":123,"text":"if you can ' t give me a date","depth":17},{"id":124,"text":"when the Constitution changes ? \"","depth":16},{"id":125,"text":"Justice Scalia said .","depth":15},{"id":126,"text":"After the court session ended ,","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"many media pundits concluded","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"that Proposition 8 has no chance","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"of being upheld ,","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"and the only questions are how the court would strike it down .","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"If the court dismisses the case with no ruling at all ,","depth":8},{"id":132,"text":"it is widely believed that an outcome would almost certainly allow gay marriages to resume in California .","depth":8},{"id":133,"text":"The session ,","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"which ran about 80 minutes long ,","depth":7},{"id":135,"text":"riveted the 400 people in the courtroom ,","depth":7},{"id":136,"text":"which included actor-director Rob Reiner ,","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"who opposes Proposition 8 ;","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"and leading gay-rights lawyers","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"including Mary L. Bonauto of the Gay and Lesbian Advocates and Defenders , and Evan Wolfson , leader of Freedom to Marry .","depth":9},{"id":140,"text":"Andrew Pugno , general counsel of ProtectMarriage.com ,","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"which petitioned the court with Dennis Hollingsworth and others ,","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"to hear its case","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"to uphold Proposition 8 ,","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"said","depth":8},{"id":145,"text":"he thought","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"the hearing went \" very well \"","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"and that Mr. Cooper spoke clearly on their behalf .","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"\" We have every confidence","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"that the nine justices will resist the political pressure","depth":10},{"id":150,"text":"to prematurely end the national debate about the definition of marriage , \"","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"he said ,","depth":8},{"id":152,"text":"adding","depth":8},{"id":153,"text":"that gay marriage is \" a social experiment","depth":9},{"id":154,"text":"that needs no special protection by or recognition from the U.S. Supreme Court . \"","depth":9},{"id":155,"text":"President Obama ,","depth":8},{"id":156,"text":"who personally supports same-sex marriage ,","depth":8},{"id":157,"text":"received updates at the White House on Tuesday about the oral arguments ,","depth":7},{"id":158,"text":"and senior adviser Valerie Jarrett and White House counsel Kathryn Ruemmler were among the White House officials","depth":7},{"id":159,"text":"who attended the oral arguments .","depth":7},{"id":160,"text":"White House press secretary Jay Carney said","depth":7},{"id":161,"text":"public officials","depth":9},{"id":162,"text":"who are expressing support for same-sex marriage ,","depth":10},{"id":163,"text":"and polls","depth":11},{"id":164,"text":"reflecting more public support for it ,","depth":11},{"id":165,"text":"are a \" welcome phenomenon . \"","depth":8},{"id":166,"text":"\" The president has noted ... the transformation","depth":9},{"id":167,"text":"that ' s been taking place in American society on these issues , \"","depth":9},{"id":168,"text":"Mr. Carney said .","depth":8},{"id":169,"text":"\" It is a recognition by an increasing number of Americans","depth":9},{"id":170,"text":"that gay and lesbian Americans ought not to be discriminated against .","depth":9},{"id":171,"text":"And it reflects his core beliefs on these issues . \"","depth":8},{"id":172,"text":"Mr. Verrilli ,","depth":8},{"id":173,"text":"representing the Justice Department ,","depth":8},{"id":174,"text":"also took part in Tuesday ' s oral arguments ,","depth":7},{"id":175,"text":"saying in part","depth":7},{"id":176,"text":"that states with same-sex \" civil unions \" also should be required to accept full recognition of gay marriage as well .","depth":7},{"id":177,"text":"Mr. Verrilli is back in court on Wednesday","depth":6},{"id":178,"text":"to agree with a lesbian widow","depth":7},{"id":179,"text":"that the federal Defense of Marriage Act of 1996 is unconstitutional .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":359,"left":194,"right":358,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":194,"left":184,"right":193,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":184,"left":0,"right":183,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":183,"left":1,"right":182,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":182,"left":2,"right":181,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":181,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":193,"left":190,"right":192,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":190,"left":5,"right":189,"relati